TASK_SCHEMA_VERSION=3
TASK_ID=455
TASK_TITLE=Cozy conversational mode: doey should chat with you, not reject you
TASK_STATUS=done
TASK_TYPE=feature
TASK_CREATED_BY=boss
TASK_TEAM=W5
TASK_DESCRIPTION=When a user types natural language at the doey CLI (e.g. 'doey please tell me about doey'), instead of the cold 'Not a valid command' error, doey should engage in a warm, cozy conversation. Use the existing Haiku primitive to power a small friendly chat. The intent fallback should detect when the input is conversational (not a mistyped command) and route to a chat mode that feels like talking to a companion. Back-and-forth should be possible — not just a single response. Think of it as 'doey chat' but triggered naturally when you just talk to it. The current UX feels like a brick wall. The new UX should feel like a friend who's happy to hear from you.
TASK_SUBTASKS=1:W5: Implement conversational chat mode in intent fallback (2 workers, parallel):done\n2:W5.1: Implement CHAT classification and chat response function in intent-fallback.sh:done\n3:W5.2: Implement CHAT dispatch case and REPL loop in doey-intent-dispatch.sh:done\n4:W5.1: Verify chat mode implementation — syntax, compat, code review:done\n5:W5.1: Re-apply CHAT classification to intent-fallback.sh (changes lost):done\n6:W5.2: Re-apply CHAT dispatch + REPL to doey-intent-dispatch.sh (changes lost):done\n7:W6: Re-implement (consolidated with 451+456) after changes lost:done\n8:W5.1: Revert unintended changes + verify target files:done
